article.headline: USC 64, UCLA 51
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Ebony Hoffman scored 17 points and pulled
down 11 rebounds in USC's 64-51 victory over UCLA Sunday.

Jessica Cheeks added 17 points for the Trojans (4-5), who raced
out to a 12-4 lead to start the game and never trailed. Cheeks made
three of USC's first five field goals.

USC led 31-20 at halftime, but both teams started the second
half slowly, combining for just four points in the first five
minutes.

UCLA (4-5) then pulled closer, using a 12-2 run to make the
score 37-34, and got within one at 41-40 two minutes later.

But a string of 3-pointers by Hoffman and Cheeks put USC ahead
by 10, and the Trojans made seven of nine free throws down the
stretch to seal the win.

Nikki Blue led UCLA with 14 points and Whitney Jones had 12.
Noelle Quinn added nine points and 10 rebounds.

Both teams shot poorly from the field. USC went 23-for-65 for
35.4 percent and UCLA was 18-for-56 for 32.1 percent
